com.inqwell.any

Class AnyString

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.inqwell.any.AbstractValue
      • com.inqwell.any.ConstString
        • com.inqwell.any.AnyString
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Any, StringI, Value, Serializable, Cloneable, Comparable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NativeDescriptor.EnumString

    public class AnyString
extends ConstString
implements StringI, Cloneable
    Concrete class AnyString. String data type of Any. The underlying implementation is the java.lang.String class. While objects of class AnyString are mutable it is generally expected that once created AnyString objects will not change. If a new value is assigned the underlying String object is re-created.

    Serialized Form

        public Any bestowConstness()
        Description copied from interface: Any
        If possible, return a const version of this. This method may return this even if this is non-const, that is this method is not bound to return a const version of the instance or even throw if it cannot (at the moment).
        Specified by:
        bestowConstness in interface Any
        Overrides:
        bestowConstness in class ConstString
        Returns:
        A const version of this. The return value has the same property values and behaviour as the original;

        this if the instance is already const;

        this if the instance does not properly implement constness, in which case Any.isConst() may still return false.
